@realmoney Mar 08, 2023 | 06:10 AM EST DOUG KASS Not a Profound Move - But a Move Nonetheless... Yesterday's sizeable market decline (-65 handles) took the S&P Index to within 2% of my calculation of "intrinsic value" (3900 on the S&P).

Remember in a "fairly valued market" there are always attractive individual equities to purchase - and attractive shorts! After the close of the market I moved from small net short to small net long - added Indexes. @tomkeene @ferrotv @lisaabramowicz1 @jimcramer

Investors/traders and the business media are becoming increasingly hyperbolic about the market's outlook (in a new regime of heightened volatility). Perhaps, as explored in @realmoney this morning we are simply in a trading range (S&P 3700-4100) and not doom/gloom (M Wilson)

nor euphoria (T Lee @fundstrat). This likely scenario could spell frustration for both bulls and bears (and for Fin TV!) @jimcramer @tomkeene @FerroTV @andrewrsorkin @ScottWapnerCNBC @riskreversal @guyadami @business @cnbcfastmoney @SaraEisen @carlquintanilla
